#Assuming that the restaurant is in the categories Restaurants, Carry out and Snack BAR
list05=[]
for ind in df.index:
    if (df['Category'][ind] == 'Restaurant') or (df['Category'][ind] == 'Carry Out') or (df['Category'][ind] == 'Snack Bar'):
#df['Restaurants'][ind]=1
        #print(df['Category'][ind])
       list05.append(1)
    elif(df['Category'][ind] != 'Restaurant') or (df['Category'][ind] != 'Carry Out') or (df['Category'][ind] != 'Snack Bar'):
       # df['Restaurants'][ind]=0
        #print(df['Category'][ind])
#df['Restaurants'].head()
        list05.append(0)
df['Restaurants']=pd.DataFrame(list05)

#1.3
#Checking if the columns in violations contains the value of 'Out of Compliance' then print 1 in the row of each column


violations=['Food from Approved Source (C)','Food Protected from Contamination (C)', 'Ill Workers Restricted (C)',
       'Proper Hand Washing (C)', 'Cooling Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Cold Holding Temperature (C)', 'Hot Holding Temperature (C)',
       'Cooking Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Reheating Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Hot and Cold Running Water Provided (C)', 'Proper Sewage Disposal (C)',
       'Toxic Substances & Pesticides', 'Rodent and Insects',
       'Nutritional Labeling', 'Trans Fat Ban', 'No-Smoking Sign Posted']


l=[]

for x in violations:
    l=[]
    for ind in df.index:
        
        if(df[x][ind]=='Out of Compliance'):
        #print(islong)
            #print(1)
            #print(df['Food from Approved Source (C)'][ind])
            l.append(1)
            #df['Insects'][ind]=1
        #return 0
        elif(df[x][ind]=='In Compliance'):
          
            l.append(0)
           
        elif(df[x][ind]=='Not applicable'):

            l.append(np.nan)
            #df['Insects'][ind]=np.nan
  #print(S)
    df[x]=l



    #print(df5['Rodent and Insects'])

#1.4
#If any of the columns contains more than 1 row with value 'Out of Compliance' 
#then count the no of rows with the value and display that as Count of Violations 
#and if the Count of Violations is more than 1 then Display new column violated as 1

h=[]
df['Count of violation']=(df[['Food from Approved Source (C)','Food Protected from Contamination (C)', 'Ill Workers Restricted (C)',
       'Proper Hand Washing (C)', 'Cooling Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Cold Holding Temperature (C)', 'Hot Holding Temperature (C)',
       'Cooking Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Reheating Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Hot and Cold Running Water Provided (C)', 'Proper Sewage Disposal (C)',
       'Toxic Substances & Pesticides', 'Rodent and Insects',
       'Nutritional Labeling', 'Trans Fat Ban', 'No-Smoking Sign Posted']]==1).sum(axis=1)

for ind in df.index:
    if(df['Count of violation'][ind]>=1):
        h.append(1)
        
    elif(df['Count of violation'][ind]<1):
        h.append(0)

df7=df
df7=pd.DataFrame(h)
df7.head()

df['Violated']=pd.DataFrame(h)

#The table has the number of violations by violation type. 
#The table has been sorted by most common to least common violations. 

df99=(df[['Food from Approved Source (C)','Food Protected from Contamination (C)', 'Ill Workers Restricted (C)',
       'Proper Hand Washing (C)', 'Cooling Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Cold Holding Temperature (C)', 'Hot Holding Temperature (C)',
       'Cooking Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Reheating Time and Temperature (C)',
       'Hot and Cold Running Water Provided (C)', 'Proper Sewage Disposal (C)',
       'Toxic Substances & Pesticides', 'Rodent and Insects',
       'Nutritional Labeling', 'Trans Fat Ban', 'No-Smoking Sign Posted']]==1).sum(axis=0).reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'Violation Type', 0: 'Number of violations'}).sort_values(by=['Number of violations'],ascending=False)

In [17]:
#3.2

#Line graph that shows the percent of restaurant inspections that have at least one violation by month and year.
#Using agg we find percentage of restaurants that have one or more violations out of all restaurants with 0 or more violations


df05=df[df['Restaurants']==1]

line=df05.groupby(by='Year and month')['Violated'].agg(lambda g: g.sum()/g.count()*100).reset_index().rename(columns={'Violated':'percentage'}).set_index('Year and month')
sns.set(font_scale=1.7)
line.plot(figsize=(15, 10), linewidth=2.5, color='blue')
plt.xlabel("Date", labelpad=10)
plt.ylabel("Percentage", labelpad=10)
plt.title("Percantage of restaurant Inspections with atleast one violation", y=1.02, fontsize=22);
In [ ]:

The percentage of restaurant having atleast one violation is forms a peak around August and September and reduces around October. It increases from May to August and September.¶
